{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ListItemFactoryProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ObjectProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is one of the core concepts of handling list widgets such"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListView"},{"type":"text","text":"] or [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/GridView"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":" is tasked with creating widgets for items"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"taken from the model when the views need them and updating them as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the items displayed by the view change."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A view is usually only able to display anything after both a factory"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and a model have been set on the view. So it is important that you do"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not skip this step when setting up your first view."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because views do not display the whole list at once but only a few"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"items, they only need to maintain a few widgets at a time. They will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instruct the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":" to create these widgets and bind them"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the items that are currently displayed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As the list model changes or the user scrolls to the list, the items will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"change and the view will instruct the factory to bind the widgets to those"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"new items."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The actual widgets used for displaying those widgets is provided by you."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the factory needs widgets created, it will create a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListItem"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and hand it to your code to set up a widget for. This list item will provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"various properties with information about what item to display and provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you with some opportunities to configure its behavior. See the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListItem"},{"type":"text","text":"] documentation for further details."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Various implementations of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":" exist to allow you different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"ways to provide those widgets. The most common implementations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/BuilderListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":"] which takes a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkBuilder"},{"type":"text","text":" .ui file"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and then creates widgets and manages everything automatically from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information in that file and [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SignalListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":"] which allows"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you to connect to signals with your own code and retain full control over"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how the widgets are setup and managed."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":" is supposed to be final - that means its behavior should"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not change and the first widget created from it should behave the same way as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the last widget created from it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If you intend to do changes to the behavior, it is recommended that you create"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":" which will allow the views to recreate its widgets."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you have chosen your factory and created it, you need to set it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the view widget you want to use it with, such as via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gtk.ListView.set_factory"},{"type":"text","text":"]. Reusing factories across different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"views is allowed, but very uncommon."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListItemFactoryProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GtkListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListItemFactory"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListItemFactoryRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gtk\/listitemfactoryprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/Gtk\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/BuilderListItemFactoryProtocol","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SignalListItemFactoryProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherited By","type":"inheritedBy"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/BuilderListItemFactory","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/BuilderListItemFactoryRef","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListItemFactory","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListItemFactoryRef","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SignalListItemFactory","doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/SignalListItemFactoryRef"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforming Types","type":"conformingTypes"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gtk\/documentation\/Gtk\/ListItemFactoryProto